## <a id="unregister"></a> Unregister App from SSO

To unregister an app from SSO, do one of the following:

+ If you configured a PCF app in [Set Up Apps to Use SSO](#set-up) above,
see [Unregister a PCF App](#unregister-pcf) below.

+ If you registered an externally hosted app using service keys in
[Register an Externally Hosted App Using Service Keys](#register-service-keys) above,
see [Unregister an Externally Hosted App Using Service Keys](#unregister-service-keys) below.

+ If you registered an externally hosted app using the SSO Developer Dashboard in
[Register an Externally Hosted App Using the SSO Developer Dashboard](#register-dashboard) above,
see [Unregister an Externally Hosted App Using the SSO Developer Dashboard](#unregister-dashboard) below.

### <a id="unregister-pcf"></a> Unregister a PCF App

To unregister a PCF app, run the following command:

```
cf unbind-service APP-NAME INSTANCE-NAME
```

Where:

+ `APP-NAME` is the name of your app.
+ `INSTANCE-NAME` is the name of the service instance you are binding.

For more information about the `cf unbind-service` command,
see [unbind-service](https://cli.cloudfoundry.org/en-US/cf/unbind-service.html)
in the Cloud Foundry CLI Reference Guide.

<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> If you delete a PCF app, the app is automatically unregistered from SSO.</p>

### <a id="unregister-service-keys"></a> Unregister an Externally Hosted App Using Service Keys

To unregister an externally hosted app using service keys, run the following command:

```
cf delete-service-key INSTANCE-NAME SERVICE-KEY
```
Where:

+ `INSTANCE-NAME` is the name of your service instance.
+ `SERVICE-KEY` is the name you want for your service key.

For more information about the `cf delete-service-key` command, see [delete-service-key](https://cli.cloudfoundry.org/en-US/cf/delete-service-key.html) in the Cloud Foundry CLI Reference Guide.

### <a id="unregister-dashboard"></a> Unregister an Externally Hosted App Using the SSO Developer Dashboard

To unregister an externally hosted app using the SSO Developer Dashboard, do the following:

1. To navigate to the Service Instance Developer Dashboard, do the procedure in [Access Service Instance Developer Dashboard](../manage-service-instances.html#access-svc-instance-developer-dashboard).
3. Click your app.
4. Click **Delete App** at the bottom of the page.
5. When prompted, click **Delete App** to confirm that you want to delete the app
   and its configurations.

	<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong>
		Deleting an externally hosted app removes the app and its
		configurations from the SSO Developer Dashboard.
		However, it still exists on your hosted platform.</p>
